"A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture Isaac Llorente-Saguer1 1Independent Researcher, London, United Kingdom illorentes@gmail","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
"com March 10, 2026 Abstract We present a fully device-resident, multi-GPU architecture for the large-scale computational verification of Goldbach’s conjecture","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" In prior work, a segmented double-sieve eliminated monolithic VRAM bottlenecks but remained constrained by host-side sieve construction and PCIe transfer latency","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" In this work, we migrate the entire segment generation pipeline to the GPU using highly optimised L1 shared-memory tiling, achieving near-zero host-device communication during the critical verification path","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
" To fully leverage heterogeneous multi-GPU clusters, we introduce an asynchronous, lock-free work-stealing pool that replaces static workload partitioning with atomic segment claiming, enabling 99","A Lock-Free, Fully GPU-Resident Architecture for the Verification of Goldbach’s Conjecture"
