3 Metrics We assess model performance from two perspec- tives: interaction quality and code correctness,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Interaction Quality The interaction quality is assessed by an evaluator model, which assesses the output for guidance, logic, relevance, coher- ence and conciseness",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Following KIEval (Yu et al,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
", 2024b), we implement a scoring system to quantita- tively grade model performance in different aspects",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Responses are rated on a definitive scale from 1 to 4 for each aspect, where 1 and 4 denote ‘Poor’ and ‘Strong’ performance, respectively, as detailed in Table 3",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 These scores are designed to encourage decisive evaluations,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" To facilitate comparison, we normalize the scores, ensuring that a rating of 1",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
0 indicates perfect performance,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" We utilize GPT-4o as the evaluator, run 5 times and average the results",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 Code correctness We evaluate code correctness using two functional-level metrics and two overall- level metrics to respectively measure correctness of functions as code snippet and complete code: • F-ESR represents the functional execution suc- cess rate across the entire test set to measure the model’s basic coding capability,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" • F-Acc represents the functional accuracy of the code, assessed through black-box testing to de- termine if the generated code is correct",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" Specifi- cally, we replace player input with random input and, for each run, fix the random seed",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 We then compare the resulting game states after multiple turns until the game ends of the generated code with the ground truth,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" We conduct 40 runs, each with a different random seed, for every entry",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
" If all runs produce identical states, the code is considered correct",Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 • ESR represents the execution success rate of the complete code of a custom game,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
 • Acc represents the accuracy of the complete code of a custom game,Game Development as Human-LLM Interaction
